caugi -- licensing notes
=========================

The caugi R package is released under the MIT License (see the `LICENSE` and
`LICENSE.md` files), with the single exception described in section 1 below.

This file summarises the licensing of bundled third-party material, as expected
by CRAN for packages that vendor Rust sources
(https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/using_rust.html). Copyright holders of
the bundled material are also recorded in the `Authors@R` field of `DESCRIPTION`
via the `cph`/`ctb` roles.


1. Adjustment Identification Distance -- MPL-2.0
------------------------------------------------

Two files are derived from the `gadjid` crate
(https://github.com/CausalDisco/gadjid) by Leonard Henckel, Theo Würtzen and
Sebastian Weichwald (Henckel, Würtzen & Weichwald, "Adjustment Identification
Distance: A gadjid for Causal Structure Learning", UAI 2024,
doi:10.48550/arXiv.2402.08616):

    src/rust/src/graph/aid.rs   -- the AID implementation, adapted from gadjid
    tests/testthat/test-aid.R   -- AID test fixtures and expected values copied
                                   from gadjid's tests

As derivatives of that source, these two files are licensed under the Mozilla
Public License, Version 2.0 (MPL-2.0, https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/), as recorded
in their SPDX headers. MPL-2.0 is a file-level (weak) copyleft licence that is
compatible with the MIT licence used by the remainder of caugi; the
corresponding source is distributed within this package. No other files in caugi
are under the MPL.


2. Bundled (vendored) Rust crates
----------------------------------

To permit offline compilation, the package vendors its Rust dependencies under
`src/rust/vendor/` and in the xz archive `src/rust/vendor.tar.xz`. Each crate
retains its own licence file(s) within its vendored directory. All are under
permissive licences:

    crate              license
    -----              -------
    bitflags           MIT OR Apache-2.0
    equivalent         Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    extendr-api        MIT
    extendr-ffi        MIT
    extendr-macros     MIT
    fixedbitset        MIT OR Apache-2.0
    foldhash           Zlib
    hashbrown          MIT OR Apache-2.0
    indexmap           Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    itoa               MIT OR Apache-2.0
    lazy_static        MIT OR Apache-2.0
    log                MIT OR Apache-2.0
    memchr             Unlicense OR MIT
    once_cell          MIT OR Apache-2.0
    paste              MIT OR Apache-2.0
    petgraph           MIT OR Apache-2.0
    proc-macro2        MIT OR Apache-2.0
    quick-xml          MIT
    quote              MIT OR Apache-2.0
    readonly           MIT OR Apache-2.0
    rust-sugiyama      MIT
    rustc-hash         Apache-2.0 OR MIT
    serde              MIT OR Apache-2.0
    serde_core         MIT OR Apache-2.0
    serde_derive       MIT OR Apache-2.0
    serde_json         MIT OR Apache-2.0
    syn                MIT OR Apache-2.0
    unicode-ident      (MIT OR Apache-2.0) AND Unicode-3.0
    zmij               MIT

For crates offered under a disjunction ("A OR B"), caugi relies on either
option; the full licence texts are included in each crate's vendored directory.
